翻译成中文：38.1The Landlord may re-enter the Property (or any part of the Property in the name of the whole) at any time after any of the following occurs:
(a)any rent is unpaid 7 days after becoming payable whether it has been formally demanded or not;
(b)there is a material breach by the Tenant of any covenant or other term of this Lease or in any document expressed to be supplemental to this Lease which is not remedied within a reasonable period of the Tenant having been notified in writing of such breach by the Landlord or;
(c)an individual Tenant becomes bankrupt;
(d)a company Tenant enters into liquidation whether compulsory or voluntary (but not if the liquidation is for amalgamation or reconstruction of a solvency company)
(e)a company Tenant has a receiver or manager appointed (including an administrative receiver) in respect of it; or
(f)the Tenant enters into an arrangement for the benefit of its creditors then and in any such case the Landlord may re-enter the Premises ) or any part of them in the name of the whole) at any time and then the Term will absolutely cease but without prejudice to any rights or remedies which may accrued to either party against the other in respect of any breach of covenant or other term of this Lease;
